Download: "azure cli"  from https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/install-azure-cli-windows?view=azure-cli-latest&pivots=msi
and "azure function app" from  https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-functions/functions-run-local?tabs=windows%2Cisolated-process%2Cnode-v4%2Cpython-v2%2Chttp-trigger%2Ccontainer-apps&pivots=programming-language-python#install-the-azure-functions-core-tools

In command propmt:
1. Log in to Azure :
az login   #This opens a browser for authentication.

If you encounter a problem "No subscriptions found" try : az login --use-device-code

note that You need a Resource Group and a Storage Account before creating the Function App.

2. Create the Function App :
az functionapp create \
  --resource-group <RESOURCEGROUP> \
  --consumption-plan-location eastus2 \
  --runtime python \
  --runtime-version 3.10 \
  --functions-version 4 \
  --name my-chatbot-func \
  --storage-account <STORAGEACCOUNT> \
  --os-type Linux
 
3.Publish Function Code to Azure:    
func azure functionapp publish my-chatbot-func --python      #This command uploads your local code to the Function App

4.List Deployed Functions and Endpoints:
az functionapp function list \
  --name my-chatbot-func \
  --resource-group <RESOURCEGROUP>\
  --query "[].invokeUrlTemplate" -o tsv       #This shows the full HTTP trigger URLs for your deployed functions.

5.Example Endpoint Test:
https://<FUNCTION_APP_NAME>.azurewebsites.net/api/<FUNCTION_NAME>?message=Hello
